@startuml
title PolyFrame State Diagram

state "KEYFRAME" as KF {
  state "Full Coefficients" as FullCoeff
  state "Complete Scene" as CompleteScene
}
state "DELTA_FRAME" as DF {
  state "Delta Coefficients" as DeltaCoeff
  state "Reference to Keyframe" as KeyRef
}
state "EVALUATED" as Eval
state "RENDERED" as Rendered

[*] --> KF : Initial frame
KF --> DF : Keyframe interval reached
DF --> DF : Consecutive delta frames
DF --> KF : Next keyframe interval

KF --> Eval : Evaluate polynomials
DF --> Eval : Apply delta + evaluate

Eval --> Rendered : Render to image
Rendered --> Eval : Re-render (zoom/pan)

KF --> [*] : End of video
DF --> [*] : End of video

note top of KF
  Keyframe contains full
  coefficient data for all
  polynomial objects
end note

note bottom of DF
  Delta frame stores only
  coefficient differences
  from last keyframe
end note

@enduml
